WEBVTT

1
00:01:35.095 --> 00:01:36.221
Wow.

2
00:01:49.735 --> 00:01:50.777
Hi. Millie!

3
00:01:50.861 --> 00:01:53.280
Hi. Mrs. Winchester!

4
00:01:53.363 --> 00:01:54.364
So nice to meet you.

5
00:01:54.448 --> 00:01:55.657
Please call me Nina.

6
00:01:55.741 --> 00:01:57.618
I've got some tea for us
and a charcuterie board.

7
00:01:57.701 --> 00:01:59.161
Is it too early for meat and cheese?

8
00:01:59.244 --> 00:02:02.205
You know. that's what they have
for breakfast in Europe.

9
00:02:03.624 --> 00:02:07.336
Wow. um. you're just.
this is... I...

10
00:02:07.419 --> 00:02:08.962
I... I...

11
00:02:09.713 --> 00:02:12.841
I'm just gonna say. I think
you might be overqualified for this job

12
00:02:12.924 --> 00:02:14.926
with all this experience
and a college degree.

13
00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:16.136
No. I know.

14
00:02:16.219 --> 00:02:18.805
I just realized I really enjoy
being a housemaid.

15
00:02:18.889 --> 00:02:19.931
You do?

16
00:02:20.015 --> 00:02:21.892
For the right families. of course.

17
00:02:23.060 --> 00:02:26.188
Okay. Uh. what brought you back
to New York?

18
00:02:26.271 --> 00:02:27.314
Uh. I missed it.

19
00:02:27.814 --> 00:02:31.068
Well. I-- I really love New England.
but I-I miss being in the city.

20
00:02:31.151 --> 00:02:34.154
But you know this is
a-a live-in position. right?

21
00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:36.615
- I mentioned that in the ad. didn't I?
- Oh. yes.

22
00:02:36.698 --> 00:02:38.158
Oh. yeah. No. of course. Yes. Yes.

23
00:02:38.241 --> 00:02:39.326
Oh. God. okay.

24
00:02:39.826 --> 00:02:41.495
- I miss being near the city.

25
00:02:41.578 --> 00:02:43.205
not actually in the city.

26
00:02:43.288 --> 00:02:44.790
It's... it's a little crazy.

27
00:02:44.873 --> 00:02:48.085
Yes. I fully agree with you.

28
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:50.629
Okay. so the job is
mostly organizing. cleaning.

29
00:02:51.213 --> 00:02:52.798
light cooking. if you're up for that.

30
00:02:52.881 --> 00:02:54.216
Oh. absolutely. I-I love to cook.

31
00:02:54.299 --> 00:02:55.300
Amazing.

32
00:02:55.384 --> 00:02:57.094
And then you would be helping me
with my daughter.

33
00:02:57.177 --> 00:02:59.554
She's. uh. Cecilia. Cece.

34
00:02:59.638 --> 00:03:02.516
She's seven years old
and. well. she's amazing.

35
00:03:02.599 --> 00:03:04.059
Well. I can't wait to meet her.

36
00:03:04.142 --> 00:03:06.770
Oh. Good. Okay.

37
00:03:06.853 --> 00:03:08.647
Would you like a grand tour

38
00:03:08.730 --> 00:03:09.731
so you can...

39
00:03:10.524 --> 00:03:12.359
see what you're getting yourself into?

40
00:03:12.442 --> 00:03:13.652
Sure.

41
00:03:13.735 --> 00:03:15.570
And the kitchen.

42
00:03:16.530 --> 00:03:20.450
My husband. Andrew. designed
this entire house soup to nuts.

43
00:03:20.534 --> 00:03:21.660
He's an architect?

44
00:03:21.743 --> 00:03:23.036
No. he's in tech.

45
00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:26.790
But he pays incredible attention
to every detail.

46
00:03:26.873 --> 00:03:30.585
Now. these steps are. uh.
kind of nuts. I know.

47
00:03:30.669 --> 00:03:33.130
Andrew says I'm totally gonna
kill myself one day on these.

48
00:03:33.839 --> 00:03:34.881
I'm such a klutz.

49
00:03:35.465 --> 00:03:37.759
I should just draw
my chalk outline on the bottom

50
00:03:37.843 --> 00:03:38.969
and get it over with.

51
00:03:39.052 --> 00:03:41.179
So there's another set of stairs
on the other side of the house

52
00:03:41.263 --> 00:03:42.931
that are less Guggenheim-y.

53
00:03:43.014 --> 00:03:44.266
If you're into that.

54
00:03:49.271 --> 00:03:51.815
- Wow.
- It's basically Andrew's man cave.

55
00:03:51.898 --> 00:03:55.193
but you are welcome to use it
anytime you want. of course.

56
00:03:55.277 --> 00:03:56.486
You'd be part of the family.

57
00:03:56.570 --> 00:03:58.655
which also means
that you would definitely have

58
00:03:58.739 --> 00:04:00.991
to listen to his TED Talk about how...

59
00:04:01.616 --> 00:04:04.244
Barry Lyndon
is a misunderstood masterpiece.

60
00:04:06.621 --> 00:04:08.623
This is the upper living room.

61
00:04:08.707 --> 00:04:11.251
which we barely ever use. to be honest.

62
00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:13.670
You sure you even need a housekeeper?

63
00:04:13.754 --> 00:04:16.465
Well. actually. I'm... expecting.

64
00:04:16.548 --> 00:04:18.550
So I'm not gonna have quite so much time

65
00:04:18.633 --> 00:04:20.469
to keep everything so perfect.

66
00:04:20.552 --> 00:04:23.430
But don't tell Andrew
because it's very early

67
00:04:23.513 --> 00:04:26.558
and I want to be sure.
you know. before I tell him.

68
00:04:26.641 --> 00:04:28.059
Yeah. Congrats.

69
00:04:28.143 --> 00:04:29.728
Thank you. Hmm.

70
00:04:30.353 --> 00:04:32.063
This is Cece's room.

71
00:04:32.147 --> 00:04:33.231
Andrew even made a little

72
00:04:33.315 --> 00:04:35.859
miniature version of our house for her.

73
00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:37.319
- Isn't that sweet?
- Wow.

74
00:04:43.492 --> 00:04:45.660
So the laundry room
is in the basement.

75
00:04:45.744 --> 00:04:47.954
and that would be your bathroom

76
00:04:48.455 --> 00:04:50.415
and you would be upstairs.

77
00:04:52.334 --> 00:04:54.211
You're gonna think
it's a little bit small.

78
00:04:54.294 --> 00:04:56.421
but it's got a lot of privacy.

79
00:04:56.505 --> 00:04:58.507
and we figured that that was
the most important thing.

80
00:04:58.590 --> 00:05:00.634
Lots of light. though.

81
00:05:00.717 --> 00:05:01.927
Ta-da!

82
00:05:02.010 --> 00:05:03.804
You can make it your own. of course.

83
00:05:03.887 --> 00:05:06.306
You can hang posters
and bring in potted plants.

84
00:05:06.389 --> 00:05:08.183
You can blast your music
as loud as you want

85
00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:10.894
because we cannot hear you downstairs.

86
00:05:10.977 --> 00:05:12.020
What do you think?

87
00:05:13.688 --> 00:05:15.273
- It's perfect.
- Okay. good.

88
00:05:16.566 --> 00:05:17.484
Win!

89
00:05:17.984 --> 00:05:19.486
Well. I'm still interviewing.

90
00:05:19.569 --> 00:05:21.822
but I'm hoping to make a decision soon.

91
00:05:22.906 --> 00:05:23.907
Here you go.

92
00:05:24.491 --> 00:05:25.492
Oh. no. you don't have to do that.

93
00:05:25.575 --> 00:05:26.576
Oh. no. I insist.

94
00:05:26.660 --> 00:05:29.412
You spent your energy and your time
and your gas money to be here. Please.

95
00:05:30.497 --> 00:05:31.748
I appreciate it.

96
00:05:31.832 --> 00:05:35.210
I have a really good feeling
about this. Millie. I do.

97
00:05:35.293 --> 00:05:36.336
Me too.

98
00:05:37.003 --> 00:05:38.421
Okay. I'll be in touch.

99
00:05:39.881 --> 00:05:41.216
She won't be in touch.

100
00:05:41.299 --> 00:05:44.261
That's the last time
I'll ever set foot in that house.

101
00:05:44.344 --> 00:05:45.387
One background check.

102
00:05:45.470 --> 00:05:48.139
and she'll see that everything
on that resume is a total lie.

103
00:05:49.057 --> 00:05:50.684
I don't even wear glasses.

104
00:05:50.767 --> 00:05:52.727
I'm just... I'm trying to look legit.

105
00:05:52.811 --> 00:05:53.854
So stupid.

106
00:06:08.577 --> 00:06:10.161
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

107
00:06:13.081 --> 00:06:14.541
Um. can I get a job application?

108
00:06:14.624 --> 00:06:15.625
Yeah. sure.

109
00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:17.836
- There you go.
- Thanks.

110
00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:29.973
I knew she wouldn't call.

111
00:06:30.557 --> 00:06:32.434
Why did I even think
I had a shot at that job?

112
00:06:32.517 --> 00:06:35.228
Oh. well. at least I got $20 out of it.

113
00:06:36.938 --> 00:06:38.940
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

114
00:06:49.159 --> 00:06:50.160
Roll it down.

115
00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:54.080
Can't sleep here.

116
00:06:54.164 --> 00:06:55.916
I'm so sorry...

117
00:06:55.999 --> 00:06:57.500
I was driving from my mom's house

118
00:06:57.584 --> 00:06:59.044
and I got really sleepy. and I just--

119
00:06:59.127 --> 00:07:00.629
I-I pulled over to take a nap. I'm sorry.

120
00:07:03.298 --> 00:07:04.883
This is her actually.
Do you mind if I take it?

121
00:07:04.966 --> 00:07:06.092
She's probably freaking out.

122
00:07:06.176 --> 00:07:07.719
Don't text and drive.

123
00:07:07.802 --> 00:07:09.054
I won't. I promise.

124
00:07:12.557 --> 00:07:14.893
- Hello?
- Hi. may I speak to Millie?

125
00:07:14.976 --> 00:07:17.479
Uh. this is her. She.

126
00:07:17.562 --> 00:07:18.897
This is Nina Winchester.

127
00:07:19.439 --> 00:07:21.399
I'm calling to offer you the job.

128
00:07:21.483 --> 00:07:23.944
I mean. if you're still available.

129
00:07:24.027 --> 00:07:25.946
Uh. you've probably got
a million job offers.

130
00:07:26.029 --> 00:07:28.031
No. I mean. yes. yes. I would love to.

131
00:07:28.114 --> 00:07:30.283
Uh. when would you like me to start?

132
00:07:30.367 --> 00:07:33.870
Oh. my goodness.
As soon as possible?

133
00:07:33.954 --> 00:07:35.288
Well. what about this afternoon?

134
00:07:35.372 --> 00:07:37.582
You know what? That would be great.

135
00:07:37.666 --> 00:07:39.876
- Great.
- Anyway. gotta run. Bye. Millie.

136
00:07:40.585 --> 00:07:41.753
Yes!

137
00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:56.935
Hey!

138
00:07:58.561 --> 00:07:59.646
Hey. I'm Millie.

139
00:07:59.729 --> 00:08:01.481
Do you work for the Winchesters?

140
00:08:02.273 --> 00:08:04.734
I'm-I'm trying to get in.
but I-I don't know the code.

141
00:08:30.927 --> 00:08:31.928
Nina?

142
00:08:34.055 --> 00:08:35.306
Nina. it's Millie.

143
00:08:41.271 --> 00:08:42.272
Nina?

144
00:08:51.614 --> 00:08:53.491
Millie? Millie. Millie. Millie!

145
00:08:54.284 --> 00:08:55.702
Welcome. Hi.

146
00:08:55.785 --> 00:08:57.871
Sorry. I. um... I meant
to leave the gate open.

147
00:08:57.954 --> 00:09:00.540
Do you need me to help you
bring in your stuff from your car?

148
00:09:00.623 --> 00:09:01.958
Oh. no. this is it.

149
00:09:02.042 --> 00:09:04.169
- Great. Wow.
- Yeah.

150
00:09:04.252 --> 00:09:06.004
Yeah. no. I put the rest of it
in a storage unit.

151
00:09:06.087 --> 00:09:08.298
Okay. well. that's great.
I'm gonna put these up in your room.

152
00:09:08.381 --> 00:09:11.176
Listen. I need to write a PTA speech

153
00:09:11.259 --> 00:09:13.303
that has to be a barn burner.

154
00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:14.763
so I'm gonna be stuck in my office.

155
00:09:14.846 --> 00:09:16.681
But the cleaning supplies
are in this closet over there.

156
00:09:17.182 --> 00:09:18.767
and... um. oh.

157
00:09:19.517 --> 00:09:21.269
You're-you're not wearing your glasses.

158
00:09:21.853 --> 00:09:24.606
Oh. I-I don't... I don't wear 'em
all the time. Contacts.

159
00:09:26.232 --> 00:09:27.567
- Oh.
- Yeah.

160
00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:29.152
Yeah. you look better without them.

161
00:09:30.028 --> 00:09:31.279
Yeah. Okay.

162
00:09:31.905 --> 00:09:33.406
I'll be upstairs.

163
00:09:34.115 --> 00:09:35.658
This is gonna be fun. Millie!

164
00:09:54.928 --> 00:09:56.554
No shoes on the furniture.

165
00:10:00.225 --> 00:10:02.936
Um. hey. Hi.

166
00:10:03.019 --> 00:10:05.647
Uh. you must be... Cece.

167
00:10:06.272 --> 00:10:07.524
I'm Millie.

168
00:10:08.316 --> 00:10:09.317
Hello.

169
00:10:10.235 --> 00:10:12.403
Oh. hey. Hi! You met Millie.

170
00:10:12.487 --> 00:10:13.488
Hi. baby.

171
00:10:13.571 --> 00:10:15.365
Millie's gonna be living with us.

172
00:10:15.448 --> 00:10:17.617
and she's gonna be helping
with the cooking and the cleaning.

173
00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:18.701
And you know what?

174
00:10:18.785 --> 00:10:20.578
She might even play Candy Land with you

175
00:10:20.662 --> 00:10:22.122
if you ask her with a pretty please.

176
00:10:23.081 --> 00:10:24.290
She's gonna live with us?

177
00:10:24.374 --> 00:10:26.835
Yes. Andrew. I told you that.

178
00:10:26.918 --> 00:10:28.878
I said she was gonna be living
in the guest room in the attic.

179
00:10:30.839 --> 00:10:33.216
Doesn't this place look incredible.
Look at it.

180
00:10:36.010 --> 00:10:38.513
- Thank you.
- Well. Millie. welcome.

181
00:10:38.596 --> 00:10:40.014
Uh. thank you.

182
00:10:40.098 --> 00:10:42.016
Are you hungry? I'm sure we can
turn this dinner for three

183
00:10:42.100 --> 00:10:45.061
- into a dinner for four.
- No. I'm probably just gonna go upstairs

184
00:10:45.145 --> 00:10:47.480
and. uh. get all settled in.

185
00:10:47.564 --> 00:10:48.690
- You sure?
- If you don't mind.

186
00:10:48.773 --> 00:10:50.733
I'll just come down afterwards
and tidy up.

187
00:10:51.276 --> 00:10:53.444
Yeah. get settled. Yeah. take your time.

188
00:10:53.528 --> 00:10:54.821
We're so happy that you're here.

189
00:10:54.904 --> 00:10:56.364
You just let us know
if you change your mind.

190
00:10:57.198 --> 00:10:58.116
Thanks.

191
00:11:03.788 --> 00:11:05.707
You ordered from the wrong
Italian place again.

192
00:11:41.701 --> 00:11:43.036
Knock. knock.

193
00:11:44.495 --> 00:11:45.496
Hi.

194
00:11:45.580 --> 00:11:47.749
That window doesn't open. sadly.

195
00:11:47.832 --> 00:11:49.626
But there's a lot
of ventilation in this room.

196
00:11:49.709 --> 00:11:51.419
so you should never get stuffy in here.

197
00:11:51.502 --> 00:11:52.879
I got you some dinner.

198
00:11:52.962 --> 00:11:55.506
Andrew always over-orders.

199
00:11:55.590 --> 00:11:57.884
I put some water in the mini fridge.
did you see that?

200
00:11:57.967 --> 00:11:59.719
Yeah. I really don't want to be a pain.

201
00:11:59.802 --> 00:12:02.931
but if it is possible to try
and get the window open.

202
00:12:03.014 --> 00:12:04.641
it'd be nice to get
some fresh air in here.

203
00:12:04.724 --> 00:12:07.018
Yeah. I agree. That's a great idea.

204
00:12:07.101 --> 00:12:09.020
I will talk to the handyman about that.

205
00:12:09.103 --> 00:12:11.648
Okay. cool. Is that the guy
that's down in the yard?

206
00:12:11.731 --> 00:12:13.650
No. that's Enzo. He's the groundskeeper.

207
00:12:13.733 --> 00:12:14.734
Never mind him.

208
00:12:14.817 --> 00:12:17.153
And then if I could just get a key
for the deadbolt.

209
00:12:17.237 --> 00:12:20.114
Oh. my God. yes. The deadbolt.

210
00:12:20.198 --> 00:12:23.159
That's so creepy.

211
00:12:23.243 --> 00:12:26.704
This used to be Andrew's
storage closet for his files. Okay?

212
00:12:26.788 --> 00:12:28.039
But. oh. my God.

213
00:12:28.706 --> 00:12:30.541
closed window. deadbolt...

214
00:12:32.377 --> 00:12:33.920
What kind of monsters are we?

215
00:12:34.003 --> 00:12:35.755
- Uh...
- I will sort that out.

216
00:12:35.838 --> 00:12:37.382
Oh. before I forget. Um...

217
00:12:39.175 --> 00:12:40.927
This is for you. It's a present.

218
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:43.805
Also. just. I saw
that your phone was just really ancient.

219
00:12:43.888 --> 00:12:46.140
and I wanted you to have that

220
00:12:46.224 --> 00:12:49.018
because I uploaded the credit card onto it

221
00:12:49.102 --> 00:12:51.229
So you can use it at the grocery store
and for gas.

222
00:12:51.312 --> 00:12:53.982
Oh. um. I'll take good care of it.
Thank you.

223
00:12:54.065 --> 00:12:58.987
Honestly. I'm like. so happy
that... you're here with us.

224
00:12:59.862 --> 00:13:02.156
- Thanks.
- Can I give you a hug?

225
00:13:04.742 --> 00:13:06.536
Thank you. Millie.

226
00:13:06.619 --> 00:13:08.788
Thank you. Okay.

227
00:13:08.871 --> 00:13:10.373
Let me know if you need anything else.

228
00:13:35.815 --> 00:13:36.816
Shit.

229
00:13:49.495 --> 00:13:50.496
No. no. no.

230
00:13:52.874 --> 00:13:54.042
No. no. no.

231
00:14:07.889 --> 00:14:08.890
Nina?

232
00:14:09.515 --> 00:14:11.392
- Where are they?
- Where are what?

233
00:14:11.476 --> 00:14:13.644
My PTA notes for the meeting tonight!

234
00:14:13.728 --> 00:14:14.979
They were right here on the counter.

235
00:14:15.063 --> 00:14:16.105
and now they're not here.

236
00:14:16.189 --> 00:14:17.440
- Where are they?
- I didn't see any notes.

237
00:14:17.523 --> 00:14:18.775
Bullshit!

238
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:19.859
Where are they?

239
00:14:21.194 --> 00:14:22.362
- Nina. no. no.
- Hey.

240
00:14:22.945 --> 00:14:25.114
- Hey! What's going on?
- Millie

241
00:14:25.823 --> 00:14:27.909
threw away my notes
for the meeting tonight.

242
00:14:29.619 --> 00:14:31.204
Where are they?

243
00:14:33.247 --> 00:14:35.124
Nina. why don't we go check your office?

244
00:14:35.208 --> 00:14:37.001
I have to get up and do a speech

245
00:14:37.085 --> 00:14:38.294
in front of everybody

246
00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:39.712
and now I have nothing!

247
00:14:42.131 --> 00:14:43.800
- Nina!
- What?

248
00:14:46.219 --> 00:14:48.179
- Do you have a copy...

249
00:14:48.930 --> 00:14:50.181
...on your computer?

250
00:14:50.264 --> 00:14:52.100
I wrote them by hand!

251
00:14:52.809 --> 00:14:53.935
Oh. fuck!

252
00:14:54.644 --> 00:14:56.729
I always think better
when I write by hand.

253
00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:58.189
Where's my nail at?

254
00:15:05.613 --> 00:15:07.073
All right. Come here. come here.

255
00:15:07.156 --> 00:15:09.033
- It's okay.

256
00:15:14.163 --> 00:15:15.790
Let's take a deep breath. okay?

257
00:15:16.499 --> 00:15:18.751
- Breathe. breathe. breathe.

258
00:15:18.835 --> 00:15:21.087
- Breathe. breathe. breathe.

259
00:15:23.256 --> 00:15:25.007
- I'm gonna pick you up.

260
00:15:36.185 --> 00:15:38.896
Here's the plan.
I am going to take Cece to school.

261
00:15:38.980 --> 00:15:40.148
and you...

262
00:15:40.898 --> 00:15:43.109
you are going to take a hot shower.

263
00:15:43.192 --> 00:15:44.777
You're gonna have a nice long breakfast.

264
00:15:44.861 --> 00:15:46.696
and then you have all day
to work on your speech.

265
00:15:46.779 --> 00:15:49.365
and you can still make it
to the salon for a touch up.

266
00:15:49.949 --> 00:15:51.784
You'll have just enough time
to get your roots done.

267
00:15:51.868 --> 00:15:52.952
I love you so much.

268
00:15:53.035 --> 00:15:54.245
- I love you.
- I love you.

269
00:15:57.623 --> 00:15:59.750
You need to be more careful next time.

270
00:16:01.794 --> 00:16:03.463
You've ruined my entire day.

271
00:16:05.381 --> 00:16:06.382
I'm sorry.

272
00:16:15.433 --> 00:16:16.434
I am so sorry.

273
00:16:17.852 --> 00:16:18.895
Don-- Don't worry about it.

274
00:16:18.978 --> 00:16:21.439
I don't know what's been going on
with her lately. She's...

275
00:16:22.398 --> 00:16:24.984
she's been on a real
emotional roller coaster.

276
00:16:25.067 --> 00:16:26.694
Oh. it's probably the hor--

277
00:16:28.237 --> 00:16:30.448
Um. Mercury in retrograde.

278
00:16:30.531 --> 00:16:32.283
Didn't peg you for the star-chart type.

279
00:16:32.366 --> 00:16:33.576
Guilty.

280
00:16:36.913 --> 00:16:38.080
Let me help you clean up.

281
00:16:38.164 --> 00:16:40.041
- It's a fuckin' mess in here.
- No. no. no. I got it.

282
00:16:40.124 --> 00:16:41.584
I got it. You go get ready.

283
00:16:42.293 --> 00:16:43.628
I don't want you to be late for Cece.

284
00:16:44.795 --> 00:16:45.922
Thank you.

285
00:16:49.091 --> 00:16:51.385
- Tomorrow will be better.

286
00:16:53.638 --> 00:16:55.348
It'll be better. I promise.

287
00:16:56.057 --> 00:16:57.058
Okay.

288
00:17:02.730 --> 00:17:04.148
- Yeah.

289
00:17:04.232 --> 00:17:06.400
Cece! Let's hit the road!

290
00:17:27.004 --> 00:17:28.297
- What are you doing here?

291
00:17:29.006 --> 00:17:30.258
I work here.

292
00:17:31.384 --> 00:17:32.927
What are you doing here?

293
00:17:33.844 --> 00:17:34.929
You...

294
00:18:25.813 --> 00:18:29.275
I don't really fit in very well
with those other PTA moms.

295
00:18:30.860 --> 00:18:33.237
I guess I didn't realize
how stressed I've been.

296
00:18:33.321 --> 00:18:36.907
It's probably just all the new hormones
making you go crazy.

297
00:18:39.785 --> 00:18:41.370
I wouldn't say anything to Andrew.

298
00:18:41.454 --> 00:18:42.580
Get out.

299
00:18:43.289 --> 00:18:44.373
I have to shower.

300
00:18:44.457 --> 00:18:46.125
And you're gonna handle dinner later.

301
00:18:46.208 --> 00:18:47.209
Yeah.

302
00:18:48.294 --> 00:18:49.420
It smells amazing.

303
00:18:49.503 --> 00:18:51.213
It's chicken piccata.

304
00:18:51.297 --> 00:18:52.506
Mmm.

305
00:18:52.590 --> 00:18:54.091
Oh. I picked those up for Cece.

306
00:18:54.842 --> 00:18:56.844
Oh. these are fantastic.
She's gonna love these.

307
00:18:57.803 --> 00:18:59.096
Someone did not get her snack today.

308
00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:01.223
and she's a very hungry little ballerina.

309
00:19:03.017 --> 00:19:05.144
Why don't you get her started.
and I'll be right back down?

310
00:19:05.227 --> 00:19:06.145
Okay.

311
00:19:12.568 --> 00:19:13.819
Hey. Cece.

312
00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:15.446
how was class?

313
00:19:18.282 --> 00:19:21.369
Would you. uh. like juice or... or water?

314
00:19:21.952 --> 00:19:24.330
Juice. But this glass is dirty.

315
00:19:25.539 --> 00:19:27.208
Really? I just took it out
of the dishwasher.

316
00:19:27.291 --> 00:19:28.584
Juice is a privilege.

317
00:19:28.668 --> 00:19:30.920
Not something you drink
out of a dirty glass.

318
00:19:32.505 --> 00:19:33.547
Of course not.

319
00:19:47.186 --> 00:19:48.354
This looks amazing.

320
00:19:49.063 --> 00:19:51.732
Doesn't it. Cece?
Way better than dinosaur nuggets.

321
00:19:53.651 --> 00:19:54.652
Hey. Millie.

322
00:19:55.361 --> 00:19:57.905
why don't you grab
a place setting and join us?

323
00:19:58.906 --> 00:19:59.907
Uh...

324
00:19:59.990 --> 00:20:01.492
No. I... I already ate.

325
00:20:01.575 --> 00:20:02.618
Oh. we insist.

326
00:20:03.703 --> 00:20:04.995
Don't we. Cece?

327
00:20:07.373 --> 00:20:08.374
Um...

328
00:20:09.709 --> 00:20:11.210
I hope you guys like it.

329
00:20:33.941 --> 00:20:35.067
Come in.

330
00:20:37.403 --> 00:20:38.320
Hey.

331
00:20:39.613 --> 00:20:41.574
- Hey.
- Sorry to bother you.

332
00:20:43.200 --> 00:20:44.577
Got something for you.

333
00:20:44.660 --> 00:20:45.911
Cece insisted.

334
00:20:46.954 --> 00:20:48.748
- She's so sweet.
- Yeah.

335
00:21:08.309 --> 00:21:09.602
No. no. no.

336
00:21:09.685 --> 00:21:11.812
Absolutely fucking not!

337
00:21:12.897 --> 00:21:13.898
Oh. my God.

338
00:21:22.823 --> 00:21:24.784
I want you to feel safe here.

339
00:21:26.911 --> 00:21:27.912
I do.

340
00:21:30.915 --> 00:21:32.500
For your door. as requested.

341
00:21:33.083 --> 00:21:34.001
Thanks.

342
00:21:38.380 --> 00:21:40.549
So how was last night? With Andrew?

343
00:21:42.092 --> 00:21:43.093
Good.

344
00:21:43.719 --> 00:21:45.262
I made chicken piccata.

345
00:21:46.555 --> 00:21:48.265
He's a dream. isn't he?

346
00:21:49.934 --> 00:21:52.728
He pretends to like everything I make him.
even if he hates it.

347
00:21:58.442 --> 00:21:59.485
Mmm.

348
00:22:02.404 --> 00:22:04.323
That's a lot of bacon. Millie.

349
00:22:04.406 --> 00:22:05.991
Are you trying to kill us?

350
00:22:11.789 --> 00:22:12.957
Where are you going?

351
00:22:15.292 --> 00:22:16.502
I have...

352
00:22:16.585 --> 00:22:17.920
Saturday off.

353
00:22:18.003 --> 00:22:19.088
Isn't that what we talked about?

354
00:22:19.171 --> 00:22:21.882
No. I... I can't spare you today.

355
00:22:23.008 --> 00:22:25.010
I missed my hair salon appointment

356
00:22:25.094 --> 00:22:28.347
because you threw away
my notes.

357
00:22:28.430 --> 00:22:29.557
Remember?

358
00:22:30.224 --> 00:22:33.018
I-I have a meeting that I can't miss.

359
00:22:34.478 --> 00:22:35.646
You have a meeting?

360
00:22:36.397 --> 00:22:37.648
What's the meeting for?

361
00:22:40.734 --> 00:22:42.236
If I could just have a couple hours off.

362
00:22:42.319 --> 00:22:43.320
and then I'll come back.

363
00:22:43.404 --> 00:22:45.155
Millie. absolutely not.

364
00:22:45.739 --> 00:22:47.533
- Baby?
- I can't have you-- What?

365
00:22:47.616 --> 00:22:48.909
Sweetheart. it's okay. She can go.

366
00:22:51.495 --> 00:22:53.706
- But. Andy. it's your day off.
- I know. exactly.

367
00:22:53.789 --> 00:22:56.959
And that's why we're gonna go
to the park... fly this kite.

368
00:22:57.042 --> 00:22:59.128
We've been waiting all week to fly. right?
We're doing donuts. we're doing kites.

369
00:22:59.211 --> 00:23:00.546
and then we're doing ballet.

370
00:23:02.298 --> 00:23:03.340
Go. Take your time.

371
00:23:07.344 --> 00:23:09.471
- Bye. Mama.
- Bye. baby.

372
00:23:14.935 --> 00:23:16.061
Have fun.

373
00:23:20.733 --> 00:23:21.650
Thanks.

374
00:23:27.323 --> 00:23:28.824
Hey. how are you doin'?

375
00:23:28.908 --> 00:23:29.909
I'm good.

376
00:23:30.618 --> 00:23:32.077
Still writing in your journal?

377
00:23:32.161 --> 00:23:34.747
Uh. yeah. Do you wanna read it?

378
00:23:34.830 --> 00:23:35.831
God. no.

379
00:23:35.915 --> 00:23:37.917
I have enough shit to read as it is.

380
00:23:38.709 --> 00:23:40.210
So you left the job at Charlie's?

381
00:23:41.086 --> 00:23:44.798
Well. this housekeeping job
just sort of fell into my lap.

382
00:23:44.882 --> 00:23:47.259
And it's live-in.
so I'm saving a fortune on rent.

383
00:23:47.343 --> 00:23:48.886
Okay. that's good.

384
00:23:49.428 --> 00:23:52.222
I have my new address here.

385
00:23:52.306 --> 00:23:53.933
and phone number.

386
00:23:54.016 --> 00:23:56.268
The family is really amazing.

387
00:23:56.352 --> 00:23:57.895
I feel... I feel lucky.

388
00:23:57.978 --> 00:24:00.189
Must make meeting new people
a little tough. though.

389
00:24:00.272 --> 00:24:01.690
having to live with a family.

390
00:24:01.774 --> 00:24:03.108
I mean. you would think that. right?

391
00:24:03.192 --> 00:24:07.196
But I have already met
a ton of really cool nannies.

392
00:24:07.279 --> 00:24:08.739
Any mannies in there?

393
00:24:09.907 --> 00:24:12.701
Are you asking me about my love life. Pam?

394
00:24:12.785 --> 00:24:14.161
If I know how Tinder works.

395
00:24:14.244 --> 00:24:16.997
or if I'm horn dogging all over Great Neck

396
00:24:17.081 --> 00:24:18.457
because I haven't gotten laid
in ten years?

397
00:24:18.540 --> 00:24:21.085
No. I'm just saying
human connections are important.

398
00:24:22.503 --> 00:24:23.420
Definitely.

399
00:24:23.963 --> 00:24:25.798
But hold onto this job. Millie.

400
00:24:26.715 --> 00:24:27.967
And the living situation.

401
00:24:30.135 --> 00:24:32.346
You'll need both.
or you'll be back at Bedford

402
00:24:32.429 --> 00:24:34.932
serving the five years
left on your sentence.

403
00:24:35.599 --> 00:24:36.892
And I don't like that for you.

404
00:24:38.018 --> 00:24:39.937
I don't like that for me. either.

405
00:24:49.029 --> 00:24:50.823
- Hi. Nina. I'm just--
- I need you to pick up Cece

406
00:24:50.906 --> 00:24:53.659
from ballet class. 1:45.
and don't be late.

407
00:24:55.035 --> 00:24:57.746
Um. okay. where is it? Nina?

408
00:24:59.540 --> 00:25:00.457
What?

409
00:25:02.209 --> 00:25:03.460
Ballet school?

410
00:25:04.044 --> 00:25:05.045
Ballet class.

411
00:25:07.089 --> 00:25:08.090
Little kids.

412
00:25:08.674 --> 00:25:09.758
Fuck.

413
00:25:10.384 --> 00:25:11.802
Tendu right.

414
00:25:11.885 --> 00:25:15.180
And curtsy and open to the left.

415
00:25:15.264 --> 00:25:16.598
Foot behind you.

416
00:25:16.682 --> 00:25:19.268
Excellent. and close to first.

417
00:25:19.351 --> 00:25:21.145
Fabulous class today. Thank you.

418
00:25:21.228 --> 00:25:23.355
Let's go get our bags and shoes.

419
00:25:23.439 --> 00:25:25.691
Great job.

420
00:25:27.067 --> 00:25:28.736
Hi. Who are you looking for?

421
00:25:28.819 --> 00:25:30.029
Uh. Cece.

422
00:25:30.112 --> 00:25:31.363
Cecilia Winchester.

423
00:25:31.947 --> 00:25:33.115
Are you Nina's new girl?

424
00:25:34.116 --> 00:25:36.535
- Yes. Hi. I'm Millie.
- Hi.

425
00:25:37.995 --> 00:25:39.288
Hi!

426
00:25:39.371 --> 00:25:41.999
Cece! Hey. I'm here to pick you up.

427
00:25:42.082 --> 00:25:44.168
I'm spending the night at Emma's.

428
00:25:44.251 --> 00:25:46.879
We arranged it weeks ago.
She has all her things.

429
00:25:46.962 --> 00:25:49.965
Oh. no. no. no. Nina just called me
and asked me to pick her up.

430
00:25:50.049 --> 00:25:52.009
- so she probably changed her mind.
- Oh.

431
00:25:53.010 --> 00:25:54.553
Okay. let me check.

432
00:25:58.974 --> 00:25:59.892
Nina!

433
00:26:00.642 --> 00:26:02.019
Hi. it's Patrice.

434
00:26:02.978 --> 00:26:07.191
Your girl is here. She's insisting
she needs to pick up Cece.

435
00:26:12.488 --> 00:26:13.572
I know.

436
00:26:14.198 --> 00:26:15.365
I know.

437
00:26:15.449 --> 00:26:17.367
No. it's no problem at all.

438
00:26:17.451 --> 00:26:19.703
It's impossible to find reliable help.

439
00:26:20.579 --> 00:26:22.706
Oh. would you like to confirm?

440
00:26:25.084 --> 00:26:26.210
Have fun.

441
00:26:28.462 --> 00:26:29.838
We figured it out.

442
00:26:29.922 --> 00:26:32.091
Okay. take care. Bye.

443
00:26:33.383 --> 00:26:34.885
Wow. they really are beautiful.

444
00:26:35.385 --> 00:26:37.262
So happy we'll be able to use them.

445
00:26:37.346 --> 00:26:38.639
Mother Winchester.

446
00:26:38.722 --> 00:26:41.183
Well. the pattern is vintage. of course.

447
00:26:42.017 --> 00:26:43.060
Millie.

448
00:26:45.646 --> 00:26:47.940
I told you Cece was having
a sleepover tonight.

449
00:26:48.023 --> 00:26:49.775
There was no need to make a scene.

450
00:26:52.027 --> 00:26:55.405
This is how you allow the help
to dress in your home?

451
00:26:55.948 --> 00:26:57.908
Uh. this is Andrew's mother.
Mrs. Winchester.

452
00:26:57.991 --> 00:26:59.076
She's downsizing.

453
00:26:59.159 --> 00:27:01.411
so she has brought us her mother's china.

454
00:27:01.495 --> 00:27:02.871
- Yes.
- Isn't it lovely?

455
00:27:04.331 --> 00:27:05.749
Isn't it?

456
00:27:06.708 --> 00:27:08.085
- Yes.
- I know.

457
00:27:08.710 --> 00:27:11.171
Andrew loves these dishes.

458
00:27:11.922 --> 00:27:13.465
I want you...

459
00:27:14.049 --> 00:27:15.551
to put them somewhere safe

460
00:27:15.634 --> 00:27:18.303
'cause Nina's likely to trip over herself

461
00:27:18.387 --> 00:27:20.013
and smash them all to pieces.

462
00:27:21.348 --> 00:27:23.225
Guilty as charged.

463
00:27:23.308 --> 00:27:24.852
- Andrew!
- Oh.

464
00:27:24.935 --> 00:27:27.604
- Mother.
- Oh. Andrew. where's your tie?

465
00:27:27.688 --> 00:27:29.606
I know.
I'm too casual. I'm sorry.

466
00:27:29.690 --> 00:27:31.692
- Mwah!
- Your hair is fabulous.

467
00:27:31.775 --> 00:27:33.944
- Thank you. darling.
- Not a root in sight. Is...

468
00:27:34.486 --> 00:27:36.029
- Is that what I think it is?
-Yes. it is.

469
00:27:36.113 --> 00:27:38.031
Can't wait to eat off of those plates.

470
00:27:38.115 --> 00:27:39.658
Family heirlooms.

471
00:27:39.741 --> 00:27:41.618
- So happy it's back.
- Me too.

472
00:27:48.250 --> 00:27:50.252
This fucking window.

473
00:28:20.115 --> 00:28:21.450
Dishes are still in the sink.

474
00:28:21.533 --> 00:28:23.619
Yeah. I know.
I'm kinda lettin' em soak.

475
00:28:23.702 --> 00:28:24.912
Uh. they've been soaking

476
00:28:24.995 --> 00:28:26.788
- for three days.

477
00:28:26.872 --> 00:28:27.956
Well. now. you know. it's kinda...

478
00:28:28.040 --> 00:28:30.083
Glug. glug. glug. glug. glug. Ding.

479
00:28:30.167 --> 00:28:31.752
Glug. glug. glug.

480
00:28:31.835 --> 00:28:33.253
...home with everybody going out.

481
00:28:34.254 --> 00:28:35.297
I'm going to ask you one...

482
00:28:38.759 --> 00:28:40.385
I'm not gonna ask you what you sell.

483
00:28:40.469 --> 00:28:42.429
I'm gonna go on here to Patsy. all right?

484
00:28:42.512 --> 00:28:43.847
Ah. Family Feud.

485
00:28:44.431 --> 00:28:45.724
I'm so sorry.

486
00:28:46.308 --> 00:28:47.976
Um. I-I couldn't get some...

487
00:28:48.060 --> 00:28:49.102
- I'll leave you alone.
- No. no. Please.

488
00:28:49.186 --> 00:28:50.312
- Get out of your way.
- Sit. please. No. sit.

489
00:28:50.395 --> 00:28:51.688
Come on.

490
00:28:53.232 --> 00:28:54.274
Please stay.

491
00:28:54.858 --> 00:28:56.860
Oh. I love this show.

492
00:28:57.486 --> 00:28:58.487
Me too.

493
00:28:59.404 --> 00:29:01.865
I've only ever seen the Steve Harvey one.

494
00:29:01.949 --> 00:29:03.992
- Really? Oh. this is classic.
- Yeah.

495
00:29:04.076 --> 00:29:05.369
This is Richard Dawson.

496
00:29:05.452 --> 00:29:06.828
Fashion icon.

497
00:29:07.496 --> 00:29:09.456
- He's an OG.
- Yeah?

498
00:29:10.040 --> 00:29:12.084
He has some spectacular sideburns.

499
00:29:12.167 --> 00:29:13.460
He sure does.

500
00:29:14.044 --> 00:29:16.922
Man. my family would have killed
on this show.

501
00:29:17.005 --> 00:29:18.674
They are absolute vultures.

502
00:29:18.757 --> 00:29:19.758
Especially my mother.

503
00:29:19.841 --> 00:29:22.177
What about you? You... your. um...

504
00:29:22.261 --> 00:29:23.553
parents. are they game people?

505
00:29:25.097 --> 00:29:27.557
Uh. we don't really keep in touch anymore.

506
00:29:27.641 --> 00:29:28.642
Oh.

507
00:29:28.725 --> 00:29:29.726
I'm sorry.

508
00:29:30.686 --> 00:29:31.937
That's gotta be hard.

509
00:29:32.437 --> 00:29:34.022
Uh. not really. no.

510
00:29:34.940 --> 00:29:36.817
I mean. even if we were.
they probably wouldn't...

511
00:29:37.484 --> 00:29:38.527
be into this.

512
00:29:39.278 --> 00:29:40.946
They're kinda like the opposite of fun.

513
00:29:41.613 --> 00:29:42.698
Well. I'll tell you what.

514
00:29:44.116 --> 00:29:45.409
You can be on our team.

515
00:29:46.910 --> 00:29:48.078
It'd be me and you...

516
00:29:49.413 --> 00:29:50.497
and Nina and my mom.

517
00:29:51.081 --> 00:29:52.791
Nina's parents don't make the cut?

518
00:29:53.667 --> 00:29:55.252
They died when she was a kid.

519
00:29:56.253 --> 00:29:57.963
- That's awful.
- Yeah.

520
00:29:59.089 --> 00:30:00.549
It's a crazy story. actually.

521
00:30:00.632 --> 00:30:02.009
They died in a house fire.

522
00:30:03.218 --> 00:30:05.637
No one knows how it was started.

523
00:30:06.138 --> 00:30:07.889
Nina made it out. her parents didn't.

524
00:30:07.973 --> 00:30:10.309
