00:43:06.375 --> 00:43:08.795
It's like all the PTA bitches talk about.

791
00:43:08.878 --> 00:43:10.463
When Cece was a baby.

792
00:43:10.546 --> 00:43:13.841
Nina threw her in a tub of running water.

793
00:43:13.925 --> 00:43:15.301
then tried to off herself

794
00:43:15.384 --> 00:43:17.637
by swallowing a shit ton of pills.

795
00:43:17.720 --> 00:43:19.806
Luckily. her husband got freaked out

796
00:43:19.889 --> 00:43:21.390
when he couldn't get a hold of her.

797
00:43:21.474 --> 00:43:23.893
then called the police
for a wellness check.

798
00:43:24.519 --> 00:43:27.730
It's. like. fucked up. right?

799
00:43:28.314 --> 00:43:31.150
Great job. dancers.
Thank you.

800
00:43:31.234 --> 00:43:33.486
- Let's get our belongings.
- All right.

801
00:43:45.248 --> 00:43:47.625
- Your car smells like feet.
- Thank you.

802
00:43:52.421 --> 00:43:53.548
Hey.

803
00:43:55.466 --> 00:43:57.009
What do you know about this family?

804
00:43:57.593 --> 00:43:58.678
Sorry. no English.

805
00:43:58.761 --> 00:43:59.929
Oh. bullshit.

806
00:44:02.431 --> 00:44:03.641
I know you shouldn't be here.

807
00:44:05.184 --> 00:44:06.227
Why?

808
00:44:07.436 --> 00:44:08.521
Leave him alone.

809
00:44:11.858 --> 00:44:13.234
You've no business talking to Enzo.

810
00:44:14.944 --> 00:44:16.612
What is this?

811
00:44:17.738 --> 00:44:20.408
They're the Broadway tickets
and the hotel reservation.

812
00:44:20.491 --> 00:44:22.410
- For Saturday?
- Yeah.

813
00:44:22.493 --> 00:44:24.579
But why would I have you book tickets...

814
00:44:25.746 --> 00:44:28.499
for the day that I'm driving Cece
to arts camp in D.C.?

815
00:44:28.583 --> 00:44:30.960
- Why would I do that?
- I don't know. but you did.

816
00:44:31.043 --> 00:44:32.295
No. I didn't.

817
00:44:33.004 --> 00:44:36.632
And I assume that these are
non-refundable now. at this point?

818
00:44:36.716 --> 00:44:38.885
Nina. I-I did what you asked me to do.

819
00:44:38.968 --> 00:44:41.012
Fine. They're gonna
come out of your paycheck.

820
00:44:41.095 --> 00:44:42.930
And I'm so sorry about that.
but it was your mistake.

821
00:44:43.014 --> 00:44:44.807
and you're gonna have to cover the fee.

822
00:44:44.891 --> 00:44:46.350
Nina. I can't afford that.

823
00:44:46.434 --> 00:44:47.476
I don't care!

824
00:44:47.560 --> 00:44:49.145
It was your mistake.
You're gonna cover it.

825
00:44:49.228 --> 00:44:50.813
Nina. that's more than I have saved.

826
00:44:50.897 --> 00:44:51.814
Hey.

827
00:44:52.899 --> 00:44:54.150
- Hello.
- Hi.

828
00:44:57.862 --> 00:44:59.989
Just about cleaned out the florist.
otherwise I would have...

829
00:45:00.072 --> 00:45:01.282
I would have got you more.

830
00:45:02.658 --> 00:45:03.784
What's wrong?

831
00:45:04.702 --> 00:45:06.078
Millie booked tickets

832
00:45:06.162 --> 00:45:08.289
for a non-refundable weekend for us

833
00:45:08.372 --> 00:45:11.083
that we can't even use.

834
00:45:11.167 --> 00:45:13.336
And she's gonna have to pay for it. Sorry.

835
00:45:13.419 --> 00:45:14.879
No. she doesn't. That's okay.

836
00:45:14.962 --> 00:45:16.714
We'll just call the credit card company
and have it reversed.

837
00:45:16.797 --> 00:45:18.049
I don't think that's a thing.

838
00:45:18.132 --> 00:45:20.426
That is a thing. That's a thing.

839
00:45:20.509 --> 00:45:21.802
You don't have to pay for anything.

840
00:45:22.845 --> 00:45:23.888
Thank you.

841
00:45:24.513 --> 00:45:25.431
I'm sorry.

842
00:45:34.649 --> 00:45:35.775
Sweetheart?

843
00:45:45.534 --> 00:45:49.038
- All this stuff for a week?
- I-I don't want her to get homesick.

844
00:46:16.107 --> 00:46:18.401
Okay. Sorry. Shit. Okay.

845
00:46:18.901 --> 00:46:19.902
Sorry.

846
00:46:27.910 --> 00:46:30.955
I am so sorry. I usually get dressed
before I come out.

847
00:46:31.038 --> 00:46:33.791
No. it-it's really my fault.
I was actually just...

848
00:46:33.874 --> 00:46:35.626
I was coming to confess something to you.

849
00:46:38.254 --> 00:46:40.631
I wanted to let you know
that I couldn't get the tickets refunded.

850
00:46:42.425 --> 00:46:44.010
- Shit.
- Yeah.

851
00:46:47.388 --> 00:46:49.932
So I think you should take them

852
00:46:50.016 --> 00:46:51.392
and go to the show with a friend

853
00:46:51.976 --> 00:46:54.186
and stay in the room.
charge whatever you want.

854
00:46:54.270 --> 00:46:56.731
Room service.
I want you to enjoy yourself.

855
00:46:57.648 --> 00:46:58.649
That is...

856
00:46:59.358 --> 00:47:01.444
really nice of you. but...

857
00:47:02.236 --> 00:47:04.530
I can't. I don't have anyone I can bring.

858
00:47:04.613 --> 00:47:06.490
You gotta have somebody.

859
00:47:08.617 --> 00:47:10.202
I wish I did. but I don't.

860
00:47:16.500 --> 00:47:19.295
Okay. well. just. um...
how about you and I go?

861
00:47:20.671 --> 00:47:23.090
We can come back tonight. I can. um...

862
00:47:24.300 --> 00:47:25.593
I can sweeten the deal a little bit.

863
00:47:25.676 --> 00:47:28.512
throw in a slice of pizza.
maybe a hot apple cider?

864
00:47:29.347 --> 00:47:31.057
I'll just tell Nina that I-I...

865
00:47:31.640 --> 00:47:33.684
exchanged the tickets
and I can take her next week.

866
00:47:33.768 --> 00:47:35.895
No. I can't have you do that.

867
00:47:35.978 --> 00:47:37.980
Oh. come on. we could both use
a night out.

868
00:47:38.064 --> 00:47:40.149
I know we could. Why not?

869
00:47:40.900 --> 00:47:42.193
I mean. it's supposed to be a great show.

870
00:47:44.862 --> 00:47:45.780
Okay.

871
00:47:47.239 --> 00:47:49.033
Great. We're going.

872
00:48:07.551 --> 00:48:08.469
Great dress.

873
00:48:25.903 --> 00:48:27.113
Thanks for coming.

874
00:49:13.075 --> 00:49:14.535
- I'm hungry.
- Yeah. I'm hungry.

875
00:49:14.618 --> 00:49:16.829
- I could eat. Yeah.
- Yeah?

876
00:49:16.912 --> 00:49:18.456
Wasn't pizza a part of this deal?

877
00:49:18.539 --> 00:49:20.166
- Yeah. it was.
- Yeah?

878
00:49:20.249 --> 00:49:22.751
Yeah. You know what?
I think I got a better idea.

879
00:49:23.669 --> 00:49:25.129
Holy shit. that was amazing.

880
00:49:26.422 --> 00:49:27.715
- It was. wasn't it?
- Yeah.

881
00:49:27.798 --> 00:49:28.841
Yeah.

882
00:49:30.217 --> 00:49:32.470
This place is really fancy.

883
00:49:32.553 --> 00:49:34.138
Well. it's charming.

884
00:49:34.221 --> 00:49:36.390
- in an old New York kind of way.
- Yeah.

885
00:49:37.308 --> 00:49:40.352
I... I don't...
I don't really know what I should order.

886
00:49:40.436 --> 00:49:42.229
Well. how about we just get
one of everything?

887
00:49:42.313 --> 00:49:43.564
- Everything?
- Everything.

888
00:49:43.647 --> 00:49:45.483
- We can't do that.
- Yeah. we can.

889
00:49:49.445 --> 00:49:50.613
You like martinis?

890
00:49:51.363 --> 00:49:52.531
I guess. I don't know.

891
00:49:52.615 --> 00:49:54.408
- Well. I guess we'll find out.
- Yeah.

892
00:49:54.492 --> 00:49:55.659
To new adventures.

893
00:49:55.743 --> 00:49:56.827
Cheers.

894
00:50:01.999 --> 00:50:04.585
I mean. you're funny. you're--
you're caring. you're great with kids.

895
00:50:04.668 --> 00:50:06.712
I just don't understand
why you're cleaning people's houses.

896
00:50:06.795 --> 00:50:08.631
You should be out there
living your best life.

897
00:50:09.381 --> 00:50:11.050
And have you ever thought about what

898
00:50:11.133 --> 00:50:12.927
you want to do with your time
on this Earth?

899
00:50:14.970 --> 00:50:18.015
- I don't know. No. not really.
- Why not?

900
00:50:20.309 --> 00:50:21.393
What about you?

901
00:50:21.477 --> 00:50:22.811
Are you...

902
00:50:22.895 --> 00:50:25.064
living your best life doing...

903
00:50:25.606 --> 00:50:27.441
Um. I don't even know what you do.

904
00:50:27.525 --> 00:50:30.569
I run a data processing company
that my father left me.

905
00:50:31.153 --> 00:50:33.197
Basically. I get paid a lot of money

906
00:50:33.280 --> 00:50:34.865
to do really boring shit.

907
00:50:35.783 --> 00:50:36.825
- Gotcha.
- I mean. all I've ever

908
00:50:36.909 --> 00:50:38.327
really wanted to do

909
00:50:38.410 --> 00:50:40.955
was to be a husband
and a father. honestly.

910
00:50:41.664 --> 00:50:42.665
That's really sweet.

911
00:50:43.457 --> 00:50:44.833
What about you? Do you want kids?

912
00:50:46.669 --> 00:50:47.586
Yeah.

913
00:50:48.379 --> 00:50:49.380
Someday.

914
00:50:50.673 --> 00:50:52.341
With the right person. of course.

915
00:50:53.008 --> 00:50:54.260
I mean. I-I...

916
00:50:54.343 --> 00:50:56.595
feel like I won the lottery with Nina.
and I should feel

917
00:50:56.679 --> 00:50:59.014
- like I'm living my best life.
- But you're not?

918
00:50:59.098 --> 00:51:00.641
I love my wife.

919
00:51:00.724 --> 00:51:02.017
I really do.

920
00:51:02.643 --> 00:51:05.771
I just feel like she's angry all the time.
and I don't know why.

921
00:51:05.854 --> 00:51:08.274
I feel like every conversation
we have ends in a tirade.

922
00:51:10.067 --> 00:51:12.361
If it makes you feel
any better. same.

923
00:51:12.903 --> 00:51:15.489
I mean. she used to be
so different. She was. uh...

924
00:51:15.990 --> 00:51:17.908
She was... loving.

925
00:51:17.992 --> 00:51:20.035
and she was kind. and she was generous.

926
00:51:20.828 --> 00:51:21.954
She was affectionate.

927
00:51:22.538 --> 00:51:24.373
I mean. all I want to do is make her happy

928
00:51:25.165 --> 00:51:26.917
and I genuinely don't know how.

929
00:51:27.001 --> 00:51:28.627
Andrew. it's not you.

930
00:51:30.087 --> 00:51:31.922
- I should not have said that. I'm sorry.
- No. it's okay.

931
00:51:32.006 --> 00:51:34.592
I mean. I see the way that she treats you.
and I hate it.

932
00:51:37.094 --> 00:51:38.095
I hate it.

933
00:51:39.888 --> 00:51:41.265
I feel like I'm letting you down.

934
00:51:42.725 --> 00:51:43.684
You're not.

935
00:51:49.481 --> 00:51:51.483
Pretty sure there's
a dance floor in there.

936
00:51:55.362 --> 00:51:57.156
- You want to go dancing?
- Should we hit it?

937
00:51:59.033 --> 00:51:59.950
Yeah.

938
00:52:01.493 --> 00:52:02.703
Let's dance.

939
00:52:35.069 --> 00:52:37.363
I don't suppose you feel sober enough
to drive us home?

940
00:52:39.365 --> 00:52:40.491
Not really. no.

941
00:52:41.992 --> 00:52:43.243
I think we got a problem.

942
00:52:47.081 --> 00:52:49.667
And you're all set.

943
00:52:50.834 --> 00:52:52.711
They're not adjoining.
but they're on the same floor.

944
00:52:52.795 --> 00:52:53.837
Thanks.

945
00:52:53.921 --> 00:52:56.173
- Mm.
- Shit. my phone's dead.

946
00:52:56.256 --> 00:52:57.257
Oh.

947
00:52:58.550 --> 00:52:59.885
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

948
00:52:59.968 --> 00:53:02.554
- Of course. Have a great stay.
- Thank you.

949
00:53:30.499 --> 00:53:31.792
I'll see you in the morning.

950
00:53:34.169 --> 00:53:35.170
Good night.

951
00:54:09.496 --> 00:54:12.082
Do not blow up your life.

952
00:54:23.218 --> 00:54:24.303
Oh. shit.

953
00:54:29.057 --> 00:54:30.434
Oh. no.

954
00:54:30.517 --> 00:54:33.145
- Hey.

955
00:54:33.937 --> 00:54:34.938
What's wrong?

956
00:54:40.068 --> 00:54:42.279
- She doesn't mean it. I'll talk to her.
- She does. Andrew.

957
00:54:42.362 --> 00:54:44.072
- She does.
- Millie. come here.

958
00:54:44.156 --> 00:54:45.657
She wants
to destroy my life.

959
00:54:45.741 --> 00:54:47.117
and I-I don't know why.

960
00:54:47.201 --> 00:54:49.328
No. she doesn't. I will talk to her.

961
00:54:49.912 --> 00:54:52.164
Andrew. I know you think
that I can do better.

962
00:54:52.247 --> 00:54:53.665
but I need this job.

963
00:54:54.166 --> 00:54:56.877
I can't lose it. I-I...
I do not want to go back.

964
00:54:56.960 --> 00:55:00.631
- Go back where?

965
00:55:00.714 --> 00:55:04.009
You're not going to lose your job.
Everything is going to be okay.

966
00:55:05.135 --> 00:55:06.595
- I promise you.

967
00:55:06.678 --> 00:55:07.596
Okay?

968
00:55:09.556 --> 00:55:11.934
Don't cry. It's okay.

969
00:55:12.017 --> 00:55:13.143
It's gonna be okay.

970
00:55:28.033 --> 00:55:29.785
Take off my dress.

971
00:57:03.003 --> 00:57:04.379
Nina's coming home early.

972
00:57:05.881 --> 00:57:07.424
So we have to beat her home.

973
00:57:09.468 --> 00:57:10.594
We should get going.

974
00:57:11.345 --> 00:57:12.763
- Okay.
- Okay?

975
00:57:15.140 --> 00:57:16.475
This is gonna sound really cheesy.

976
00:57:16.558 --> 00:57:18.936
but I didn't think anybody
could look so beautiful in the morning.

977
00:57:30.155 --> 00:57:31.615
Nina can't ever know.

978
00:57:33.116 --> 00:57:35.160
And this can't ever happen again.

979
00:57:35.744 --> 00:57:37.162
I really wish things were different.

980
00:57:39.247 --> 00:57:40.707
I wish I would have met you before.

981
00:57:42.918 --> 00:57:43.919
Me too.

982
00:57:44.628 --> 00:57:45.629
Are you okay?

983
00:57:46.213 --> 00:57:47.422
Yeah.

984
00:58:16.618 --> 00:58:17.536
Nina?

985
00:58:23.375 --> 00:58:24.376
Nina!

986
00:58:26.378 --> 00:58:28.714
I'm gonna go get changed.

987
00:58:29.673 --> 00:58:32.342
I'll start making lunch
just in case she comes back.

988
00:58:50.193 --> 00:58:51.528
Ah. fuck it.

989
00:59:17.637 --> 00:59:18.638
Hello?

990
00:59:21.433 --> 00:59:22.476
Anybody home?

991
00:59:26.646 --> 00:59:28.231
- Hi.

992
00:59:29.775 --> 00:59:31.651
- Welcome home.

993
00:59:31.735 --> 00:59:34.488
- Thank you.
- Lunch is almost ready.

994
00:59:35.072 --> 00:59:37.491
Oh. boy.

995
00:59:37.574 --> 00:59:39.701
- Hi.
- Hey. sweetheart.

996
00:59:40.202 --> 00:59:43.246
- Hi. What are you doing?
- I was just fixing the drain

997
00:59:43.330 --> 00:59:45.665
in the upstairs guest bathroom.
It's a bit clogged.

998
00:59:45.749 --> 00:59:47.250
I knew you would try to do that.

999
00:59:47.334 --> 00:59:48.835
I said the plumber's coming on Tuesday.

1000
00:59:48.919 --> 00:59:50.504
No. I know. I was just
feeling extra manly today.

1001
00:59:50.587 --> 00:59:52.089
- Okay.
- Yeah.

1002
00:59:52.798 --> 00:59:54.257
How was the trip? How's Cece?

1003
00:59:54.341 --> 00:59:55.801
She's good.

1004
00:59:57.177 --> 00:59:58.095
Listen.

1005
00:59:59.179 --> 01:00:00.764
I'm very sorry about last night.

1006
01:00:02.057 --> 01:00:03.600
It was a very long drive.

1007
01:00:03.683 --> 01:00:05.143
I was very tired.

1008
01:00:05.227 --> 01:00:07.229
I do not sleep well in hotels.

1009
01:00:07.312 --> 01:00:08.438
turns out.

1010
01:00:08.522 --> 01:00:11.108
And I should not be left alone
with my phone.

1011
01:00:11.191 --> 01:00:14.778
So. lesson learned. It's a new day.

1012
01:00:14.861 --> 01:00:17.405
- Please accept my apologies.
- Yeah. it's okay.

1013
01:00:17.489 --> 01:00:19.074
- I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

1014
01:00:19.658 --> 01:00:21.368
- Let's get some food in ya.

1015
01:00:21.451 --> 01:00:22.452
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1016
01:00:22.536 --> 01:00:24.621
- Mm. Hi. Mm.
- Hi.

1017
01:00:25.872 --> 01:00:27.749
- This looks fantastic.
- Yes.

1018
01:00:31.795 --> 01:00:33.755
...you know? Hey. Millie.

1019
01:00:33.839 --> 01:00:36.383
- Mm-hmm?
- How was your night off?

1020
01:00:37.926 --> 01:00:40.470
Uh. my best friend Lexi took me

1021
01:00:40.554 --> 01:00:41.972
to Peter Luger.

1022
01:00:42.055 --> 01:00:42.973
- Hmm.
- Um.

1023
01:00:43.056 --> 01:00:44.933
she had a gift certificate.
It was really nice.

1024
01:00:45.016 --> 01:00:49.104
We had a lot of sides.
But I don't really eat meat.

1025
01:00:50.063 --> 01:00:52.357
This looks incredible. So. thank you.

1026
01:00:52.440 --> 01:00:55.944
I don't know why
but my quiches never turn out.

1027
01:00:56.027 --> 01:00:57.404
I've been meaning to ask you.

1028
01:00:57.487 --> 01:00:59.364
Did you learn how to cook
while you were in prison?

1029
01:01:02.701 --> 01:01:06.121
You know. she was in prison for ten years
before she came to work with us.

1030
01:01:07.205 --> 01:01:08.582
Right?

1031
01:01:09.708 --> 01:01:10.834
I think it's brave.

1032
01:01:11.960 --> 01:01:15.589
making a new start in a new town.

1033
01:01:15.672 --> 01:01:18.550
I'm glad that we could be
a part of your journey.

1034
01:01:24.598 --> 01:01:25.849
- Oh.

1035
01:01:26.808 --> 01:01:29.227
We need a restock
of all of Cece's favorites

1036
01:01:29.311 --> 01:01:30.353
before she gets home.

1037
01:01:30.437 --> 01:01:32.689
You haven't really been
keeping up with that.

1038
01:01:33.523 --> 01:01:36.234
And could you... Sorry.

1039
01:01:36.318 --> 01:01:38.570
Could you use my car
for running errands from now on

1040
01:01:38.653 --> 01:01:40.030
until you can save up
to get something nicer?

1041
01:01:40.113 --> 01:01:42.032
I'm afraid yours is becoming

1042
01:01:42.115 --> 01:01:44.743
an unwelcome topic
of conversation. Here you go.

1043
01:01:45.994 --> 01:01:47.454
- You know what I mean?
- Yeah.

1044
01:01:48.246 --> 01:01:50.207
